üîß How to Use GitHub (Step-by-Step)
‚úÖ 1. Create an Account
Go to: https://github.com

Sign up with your email and set a password

Choose a username

Verify your email

‚úÖ 2. Install Git (if not already)
Download Git: https://git-scm.com/downloads

Install with default settings

Open Git Bash (or command line)

‚úÖ 3. Set Up Git on Your PC (One-Time Only)
bash
Copy
Edit
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "your@email.com"
‚úÖ 4. Create a Repository
Go to your GitHub profile

Click ‚ÄúNew‚Äù in Repositories tab

Set:

Repository name (e.g., my-project)

Public or Private

Optionally: Initialize with a README

Click Create repository

‚úÖ 5. Clone the Repository to Your Computer
bash
Copy
Edit
git clone https://github.com/your-username/my-project.git
cd my-project
‚úÖ 6. Work on Your Code
Add or edit files in the folder

Use any code editor (like VS Code)

‚úÖ 7. Track and Push Changes
bash
Copy
Edit
git add .                # Track all changes
git commit -m "Your message"   # Save changes
git push origin main     # Push to GitHub
‚úÖ 8. Pull Changes from GitHub
(Useful when collaborating)

bash
Copy
Edit
git pull origin main
‚úÖ 9. Create New Branch (Optional)
bash
Copy
Edit
git checkout -b feature-branch-name
# make changes
git push origin feature-branch-name
‚úÖ 10. Create Pull Request
Go to the repository on GitHub

Click "Compare & pull request" if you pushed a new branch

Review, comment, and merge

